  "texts": [
    "Next, edge convolution is used for graph convolution, to map the relations into a 2D map score.",
    "As shown in Fig. 36, the method first uses a two-stream network to extract spatiotemporal features, after which features are sent to ActionPFGCN and BoundaryPFGCN, and then 2D map fractions are generated.",
    "Finally, the action classification score, the action regression score, the end score, and the beginning score are fused to produce a dense proposal.",
    "(GTE) for global information perception.",
    "In this way, LGTE is expected to integrate the long-term context of proposals using global groups while recovering more structure and detailed information from local groups."
